{{Quote|These newcomers took to calling themselves the Legions of Lettow, for they swore to defend us and our right to seek knowledge of the Force without the interference of the Jedi hierarchs and their pronouncements about what was correct and what was forbidden.|[[Arden Lyn]]|<ref name="TEGTW" />}}
The '''Legions of Lettow''' was the name taken by the apprentices and acolytes of the [[Kashi Mer Dynasty]] exile and [[Jedi/Legends|Jedi]] Renunciate [[Xendor]]. One of the earliest [[First Great Schism|breakaway]] sects of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], the Legions were defeated in battle at the end of a war with their Jedi cousins called the [[First Great Schism]].

==History==
During the early history of the [[Jedi Order/Legends|Jedi Order]], the [[Kashi Mer Dynasty|Kashi Mer]] exile [[Xendor]] was studying on the planet [[Ossus/Legends|Ossus]], [[Fortress world/Legends|fortress world]] of the Jedi and home to a culture devoted to the study of [[The Force/Legends|the Force]] and its [[Light side of the Force/Legends|light side aspect]] called the Ashla. A respected [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knight]], Xendor was a vocal opponent to the Order's views on the Force which he saw as "exclusionary". Among his closest allies was a [[Followers of Palawa|Follower]] and [[Steel Hand of Palawa]] named [[Arden Lyn]]; the two of them shared philosophies away from the eyes and ears of the [[Jedi High Council/Legends|Jedi High Council]] and eventually became lovers.<ref name="TEGTW" />

Xendor, able to bear his frustration no longer, approached the High Council and requested their blessings in opening a new [[Jedi academy]] far from Ossus to focus on the [[Dark side of the Force/Legends|darker aspects]] of the Force, the Bogan. When the Council refused, Xendor quietly broke with the Order and traveled to the planet [[Lettow]] to open an [[Legionnaire Academy|academy]] which focused its teachings on the Bogan. Drawing on Force traditions such as the [[Order of Dai Bendu]], the [[Followers of Palawa]], the Kashi Mer [[Guardians of the Breath|Guardians of Breath]], the [[Baran Do]], and the [[Chatos Academy]], Xendor's academy drew a trickle of interest which quickly transformed into a roaring river. Xendor and his followers embraced the dark side of the Force, rejected the idea of order and structure<ref name="TEGTW" /> and celebrated their freedom by giving in their passions and emotions and touching the power of the dark side.<ref name=":0" /> It was these acolytes which named their new group the Legions of Lettow, as they believed that they would one day be forced to defend their traditions from the Jedi High Council's wrath.<ref name="TEGTW" />

At the academy, the Legionnaires followed similar initiation ceremonies that were practiced by the Jedi Order; for example, the forging of [[Force-imbued sword/Legends|Force-imbued blades]]<ref name="TEGTW" /> was carried over from ancient [[Tythan]] practices.<ref name="NEC">''[[The New Essential Chronology]]''</ref> Initiates shaped high-carbon steel in the furnaces of the academy in an extremely challenging ritual, melding the blade's molecular lattice with that of the energy [[Lightsaber crystal/Legends|crystal]], making the blade and the crystal one-in-the-same. With the furnace-forged steel,<ref name="TEGTW" /> the Legionnaires adopted the ancient [[Jar'Kai/Legends|Jar'Kai]] fighting art, calling it [[Niman]], after the triumvirate of [[Kashi]] [[Deity/Legends|gods]].<ref name="dfs4">{{Wizards|url=default.asp?x=starwars/article/sw20050526a|series=The Dark Forces Saga|text=Part 4: Of the Crudest Matter}}</ref>

In [[24,500 BBY]], an open war that would come to be known as the [[First Great Schism]] erupted between the Legions and the Jedi Order.<ref name=":0" /> According to some historians, it was General Xendor and his Legionnaires who attacked the Jedi,<ref name="Star Wars: The Old Republic">{{TORcite|type=codex|Galactic History 13: The First Great Schism}}</ref> others say it was the Jedi Council who declared war against the Dark Legions.<ref name=":0">[[Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force (real-life book)|''Jedi vs. Sith: The Essential Guide to the Force'']]</ref> The most detailed version of the events provided by [[Inquisitorius/Legends|Imperial Grand Inquistitor]] [[Laddinare Torbin]], based on Arden Lyn's recalling of the events. According to this account, it was the Jedi Order who raised army first so the reluctant Xendor took up the title of [[General/Legends|general]] and attacked Ossus directly, to prevent bloodshed. However, during the [[Battle of Ossus (First Great Schism)|battle]], Xendor's forces were fought off and forced to commit troops to several fronts as the Order pushed the Legionnaires towards the [[Core Worlds/Legends|galaxy's core]]. Xendor then tried to warn the [[Galactic Republic/Legends|Galactic Republic]] that the Jedi Order wanted to take power under the guise of the protectors, but was ignored and branded as a warlord by the Republic.<ref name="TEGTW" />

The war between the Jedi Order and the Legions ot Lettow raged on [[Battle of Chandrila (First Great Schism)|Chandrila]], [[Battle of Metellos (First Great Schism)|Metellos]], [[Battle of Brentaal IV (First Great Schism)|Brentaal IV]] and [[Battle of Coruscant (First Great Schism)|Coruscant]] until the Jedi leader, [[Awdrysta Pina]] managed to come into direct [[Battle of Columus|battle]] with Xendor on [[Columus/Legends|Columus]]. Known as the Green Blade, Master Pina and his [[Jedi Knight/Legends|Jedi Knights]] were able to separate Xendor's vanguard from the bulk of his army through the use of a [[Force-meld|strong Force meld]] - a practice rejected by the Legionnaires since they saw it as giving up their individuality. Cutting through powerful warriors such as [[Sethul Asaiage]] and [[Tun Bohoi]], Pina eventually dueled Xendor and slew him in hand-to-hand combat.<ref name="TEGTW" />

With Xendor dead, Arden Lyn took command of the remaining Legionnaires on Lettow. As Pina's forces [[Battle of Lettow|took over]] the academy, Lyn and her followers held off the Jedi until the Legionnaires could flee Republic space. Separating from the rest of the survivors, Lyn attempted to hide beyond [[Atrisia/Legends|Kitel Phard]] but was followed by Master Pina and he finally [[Duel on Irkalla|cornered]] her on [[Irkalla]]. There, Lyn used a [[Kashi Mer talisman]] gifted to her by Xendor to channel her rage and sorrow over the loss of her lover to shatter Pina's blade and send the shards through his body. As he lay dying, Pina poured his last bit of life into attacking Lyn with the [[Morichro/Legends|Morichro]] technique, stopping her heart and nearly killing her.<ref name="TEGTW" />

==Legacy==
[[7000 BBY|17,500 years after]]<ref name=":0" /> Xendor's separation from the Order, the [[Dark Jedi/Legends|Dark Jedi]] who would eventually be known as the [[Exiles]] of the [[Hundred-Year Darkness/Legends|Hundred-Year Darkness]] believed themselves to be the heirs of the Legion of Lettow's legacy. The Exiles, banished to the [[Stygian Caldera]], established the [[Sith Empire/Legends|Sith Empire]] with a philosophy that favored the dark side of the Force.<ref name="Book of Sith: Secrets from the Dark Side">''[[Book of Sith: Secrets from the Dark Side]]''</ref>

A record from the final battle on Columus survived the conflict and was obtained by the Jedi Order. Called the [[Columus Data Card]], the files were written through audio records by [[Padawan/Legends|Padawan]] [[Danzigorro Potts]]. Describing the final battle as he lay dying, Potts described the deaths of Xendor and other former Jedi, including his own master [[Jook-jook H'broozin]] and friends [[Blendri]] and [[Cuthallox]].<ref name=":0" />

Millennia later, "[[Minions of Xendor]]!" remained a common curse among [[Smuggler/Legends|smugglers]].<ref name="The Paradise Snare">''[[The Paradise Snare]]''</ref>

==Behind the scenes==
The "Legions of Lettow" is the name of the [[Knights of Sith]] in [[George Lucas]]' [[The Star Wars first draft|first revision]] of the original script for [[Star Wars: Episode IV A New Hope|''A New Hope'']], simply entitled "The Star Wars," in which members were simply referred to as "Lettow." This script is barely recognizable from the final script used for the film.<ref name="Scripts">{{WebCite|url=https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller/the-star-wars-revised-first-draft|text=''The Star Wars: First Draft''|work=[https://www.starwarz.com/starkiller Starkiller — The Jedi Bendu Script Site]|archivedate=20240904070909}}</ref> ''[[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]'' later revealed that the "Legions of Lettow" was the name of a historical enemy of the Jedi Order<ref name="POTJ">''[[Power of the Jedi Sourcebook]]''</ref> and ''[[The New Essential Chronology]]'' identified Xendor's followers as the Legions of Lettow.<ref name="NEC" />

